    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the Teng Tools Get Organised system?",
            "answer": "<p>The <strong>Get Organised</strong> system is the core concept behind Teng Tools. Every tool set is supplied in a unique TC tray with a dedicated slot for each tool. These trays click together and fit into any Teng Tools storage solution \u2014 roller cabinets, tool chests, wall racks or portable cases. You can build a complete, customised tool kit tray by tray, and instantly see if any tool is missing from its slot.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does the Teng Tools lifetime guarantee cover?",
            "answer": "<p>The Teng Tools <strong>lifetime guarantee</strong> covers all hand tools and tool storage (when registered) against manufacturing or material defects under normal working conditions. If a tool breaks through normal use, it will be repaired or replaced. The guarantee does not cover misuse, modifications, normal wear and tear, or consumable components. Simply return the product to your retailer with proof of purchase.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is included in a Teng Tools mega master set?",
            "answer": "<p>Teng Tools mega master sets are comprehensive tool kits containing <strong>hundreds of pieces</strong> across multiple categories \u2014 typically including 1/4\", 3/8\" and 1/2\" drive socket sets, combination spanners, screwdrivers, hex keys, pliers, adjustable wrenches and specialist tools. All supplied in Get Organised TC trays. The exact contents vary by set \u2014 check individual product listings for full specifications.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Teng Tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Teng Tools range including tool sets, storage solutions and individual hand tools. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts, workshop outfitting quotes and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I mix and match Teng Tools TC trays in any storage unit?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. That is the entire point of the Get Organised system. <strong>All TC trays are the same width</strong> and click together to create any combination. You can mix socket trays, spanner trays, screwdriver trays and specialist trays in any order, then drop them into any Teng Tools roller cabinet, tool chest or carry case. This means you build exactly the tool kit you need \u2014 no duplicates, no gaps.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Where are Teng Tools manufactured?",
            "answer": "<p>Teng Tools is <strong>headquartered in Alingsas, Sweden</strong>, and owned by Bergman & Beving (a Swedish listed group founded in 1906). Tools are manufactured in Taiwan to Teng Tools' Swedish design specifications and quality standards. This combination of Scandinavian design and Taiwanese precision manufacturing delivers professional-quality tools at competitive price points.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
